        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:33PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 132 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Boswells Tavern to Fork Union to near Toga.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Fork Union, Columbia, Ferncliff, Kents Store, and Duncan around
140 PM EDT.
Louisa around 145 PM EDT.
Fife and Lakeside Village around 150 PM EDT.
Mineral and Hadensville around 155 PM EDT.
Cartersville around 200 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Orchid, Angola,
Maidens, Three Square, Bremo Bluff, Hawk, Whiteville, Michaux, West
View, and Grays Siding.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central Virginia.</instruction>
